comment.body:
@blurHY: Are you for or against Tor, I2P? These can be used for Nth room (whatever that is, is that like the infamous/fictitious "red room"?)
A backdoor is not acceptable, under any conditions and a death nail in any privacy or security oriented software (if it's found out, that is).
You promise you will only use that backdoor for those cases, but what if someone comes to your house with a crowbar and flattens your fingers until you tell them how to use the backdoor for what they want instead. Do you trust yourself not to give in under torture? The only real security/privacy is ensured by mathematics, not by "trusted" parties.
